race.comment: BURRANEER BUOY (2) has been just behind the placegetters at the past couple but prior to that had strung a hat-trick of wins together around this circuit. Handles all going and should be hitting the line with gusto. PRINCE AKEEM (9) is an honest commodity who has hit the top-five at his past 12 efforts and will be rock-hard fit for this. Nicely placed to find the winners' stall. FROM THIS MOMENT (5) is a five-time winner here on her home circuit and will strip fitter second-up from the break. Top-three credentials. KING'S HALO (4) grows a leg for hoop Wiggins who has five wins and five placings from 14 steers. In the mix on best form.
